// Datasheet for the `widget` device: the components it requires + a storage requirement. A datasheet
// describes requirements only — it never defines a shape. The `Particle` shape is defined in the
// device's impl (widget.arche), which uses it; `Particle[4]` is the storage requirement (minimum).
// The doctest drives the shape with the pool auto-provided (device doctests compile as generated
// drivers, where the requirement becomes the real allocation).
// RUN: true
pos :: float;
vel :: float;
[4]Particle;